# =============================================================================
# geometry/2D_regolith_pore_throat.opts — regolith pore channel (implicit regolith).
# Generated by preprocess/build_geometry_regolith_pore.py (deterministic).
# Study: studies/icy_regolith/implicit_pore_domain/ (Effort 1).
#
# Two-sided channel whose top/bottom walls are 12+12 lunar-regolith
# grains (R_med=5.0e-05 m), with a central throat pinch (min gap
# 37% Ly at x=0.53Lx). Ice placement strategy:
# 'throat_bridge' -> 7 ice grains in the pore space. The regolith
# is the deformed boundary, NOT a simulated field (that is Effort 2).
#
# eps=8.5840e-07 is the comp_eps.py (Kaempfer&Plapp) value for T=-20C,
# alpha_c=0.01341 (kinetic-bound limited, so grain-size independent here;
# eps/R_smallest=3.0% < 5%). Reproduces the validated
# 2D_ripening_two_sided reference exactly. PAIR ONLY with a T=-20C
# experiment (e.g. 30day_T-20_h1.00_arrh, which sets the matching
# beta_sub0/d0_sub0). RECOMPUTE eps for any other run temperature.
# =============================================================================
# DOF_GRID: 1344 446
